OPTION 1:

August 6th.
The day the first-ever website was published by Tim Berners-Lee.

Name: Webly Day
Celebrated by challenging employees to not use the web. For 1 whole day.
Source : http://www.wired.com/2011/08/world-wide-web-20-years/


OPTION 2:

March 29.
The first stable release of Weebly.

Name:  Weebday

Task given to employees - Find 2 People have never heard of Weebly to create a website or a blog using Weebly. Awards for the best submission.

Source : https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weebly